originalText.text: This was a great find in the city, we happen to walk by and see this dessert shop. Their banana pudding, and Ube pudding was really good. I like how they have unique Ube flavor with this classic dessert. The prices were more expensive then the pictures of the menu that I saw on Yelp prior to coming in. The desserts were all very sweet, maybe a bit too sweet for my taste. I would recommend to give this place a try.

originalText.text: 3.12.23 - amazingly nice staff who are patient and engaging. We tried the classic banana pudding and the ube, both of which were great! The seasonal flavors right now are Thai Ice Tea and something else I can't remember (sorry!). We were able to try samples before buying, but that was not necessary. Support local and I hope this place has a long history in the East Village.

originalText.text:
Light, fluffy and delicious banana pudding with 8-ish options (including vegan ones), better than Magnolia's . $4 for 1 scoop cup and $6 for 2 scoops with some free toppings.

I had the ube and the original and both were really good and paired well with each other. Given its lightness, I think this is a great dessert when it is too cold for ice cream or if you want a lighter dessert.

They did list other flavors but they weren't available as they are still getting a hang of foot traffic into the store and assured me that more flavors will be reliably available in April.

originalText.text: Wow I really wish there was a Baonanas near where I lived. I love banana pudding. Tried the Ube flavor, and it was awesome. Loved it so much. It was so light and airy. I also tried the original, and I may have liked it more than Ube. Can’t wait to come back!!

originalText.text: I've known about the existence of this dessert place for a while, but only got the chance to finally try it yesterday. I was NOT disappointed! I got the matchananas and ube flavors topped with strawberries and they were superb! Not too sweet, which made it enjoyable to consume. Will definitely return here someday.
